The paper deals with saliency detection, which is a computer vision task, and proposes an end-to-end deep learning framework for unsupervised saliency detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning and probabilistic modeling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various benchmarking datasets, which indicates that it could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
